  "body": "bug 1. --datadir has no effect during wallet creation, default folder .lighthouse is always used.\r\n\r\nbug 2. --datadir is ignored during account creation, default folder .lighthouse is always used.\r\n\r\nbug 3. validator process can only work normally on the default folder .lighthouse, error occurs when specifying a non-default --data-dir.\r\n\r\nError:\r\n\r\nThe validator_definitions.yml file does not contain either of the following fields for \"/home/j/test/validators/0xaa8547c87726f0b936e29a510497400b8cb8be4af5cd99d53aa2f424e231b68b2fc78a2d0c3c1e055cb65cc84bc43d48/voting-keystore.json\":\r\n\r\n - voting_keystore_password\r\n - voting_keystore_password_path\r\n\r\nYou may exit and update validator_definitions.yml or enter a password. If you choose to enter a password now then this prompt will be raised next time the validator is started.\r\n\r\nSteps taken:\r\nstep 1. create a wallet in default folder\r\nstep 2. create a validator in default folder\r\nstep 3. rename folder .lighthouse to test\r\nstep 4. launch validator process against test folder, error\r\n            command: lighthouse vc --datadir test\r\nstep 5. rename folder test back to .lighthouse\r\nstep 6. launch validator process with default folder, successfully create validator_definitions.yml\r\n            command: lighthouse vc\r\nstep 7. rename folder .lighthouse to test\r\nstep 8. edit validator_definitions.yml and replace \".lighthouse\" with \"test\"\r\nstep 9. launch validator process against test folder, error\r\n            command: lighthouse vc --datadir test\r\n\r\nPlease make --datadir work. It is much needed. Both prysm and teku work fine with the switch.\r\n",
